\n          - time: Apr 27\n        - button \"Grok actions\" [ref=e153] [nth=10]\n        - button \"More\" [ref=e154] [nth=10]\n        - text: MENU\n        - group \"359 views\":\n          - button \"0 Replies. Reply\" [ref=e155] [nth=6]\n          - button \"0 reposts. Repost\" [ref=e156] [nth=8]\n          - button \"0 Likes. Like\" [ref=e157] [nth=3]\n          - link \"359 views. View post analytics\" [ref=e158]:\n            - /url: /LucaRoland_/status/2048875835164082438/analytics\n            - text: \"359\"\n          - button \"Bookmark\" [ref=e159] [nth=9]\n          - button \"Share post\" [ref=e160] [nth=10]\n      - article \"Steve Harris @IAmSteveHarris Apr 28 Menu\" [ref=e161]:\n        - link \"Steve Harris\" [ref=e162]:\n          - /url: /IAmSteveHarris\n        - link \"@IAmSteveHarris\" [ref=e163]:\n          - /url: /IAmSteveHarris\n        - link \"Apr 28\" [ref=e164] [nth=2]:[... 723 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"ok":true,"format":"ai","targetId":"F05346B4CF61C41498A03253A5F59198","url":"https://x.com/everestchris6/status/2048855885620162603","stats":{"lines":314,"chars":15913,"refs":172,"interactive":157},"refs":172,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"browser","kind":"snapshot","format":"ai","wrapped":true}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777752648361}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bc2568a","parentId":"4cb6ac97","timestamp":"2026-05-02T20:10:57.612Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found a great example. The post from @everestchris6 (Chris) is EXACTLY what Bobby is asking about. Let me read that post carefully:\n\n**Chris's system (from the post):**\n- OpenClaw bot finds restaurants with ugly menus\n- Rebuilds them as live web menus\n- Mails the owner a postcard... on autopilot\n\n**The system works like this:**\n1. Scrapes every restaurant in a city in real time\n2. Filters by review count + rating + last menu update + photo quality\n3. Pulls the real menu items from the official site, PDF, or Google reviews\n4. Samples the brand palette from the restaurant's own visual identity\n\n\n5. Renders a brand-matched menu, hosted live at a QR-accessible URL\n6. Writes a personalized postcard referencing a real reviewer and a real dish\n7. Mails it to the registered office addressed to the owner by first name\n\nThe entire workflow from discovery through brand-matching and outreach is completely automated. Chris is even offering a free guide to people who reply \"MENU\" and retweet, and he's built a custom AI buildout service at calendly.com for anyone who wants a personalized system.\n","thinkingSignature":"e157db2933ea5daca59638f6697587037741797e7332a87e6540e7d0010a5a5a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound it. Here's what's actually working on X right now:\n\n## Real Example From X — @everestchris6\n\nHe built an OpenClaw bot that:\n1. **Scrapes every restaurant in a city** in real time\n2. **Filters** by review count + rating + last menu update + photo quality\n3. **Pulls** the real menu items from their official site, PDF, or Google reviews\n4. **Samples** the restaurant's brand palette from their own photos\n5. **Builds** a brand-matched live web menu\n6. **Writes** a personalized postcard referencing a real reviewer + real dish\n7. **Mails it** to the restaurant addressed to the owner by first name\n\nEvery step from discovery → building → outreach is fully automated.\n\nHis tweet got **436K views, 2.9K likes, 698 reposts** — and he was giving away a free guide to anyone who replied \"MENU\" + RT'd.\n\nHe also has a Calendly for custom AI buildouts if people want a personalized system built.\n\n## The Pattern Everyone's Using\n\n| Step | What They Automate |\n|---|---|\n| **Lead Finding** | Scrape Google Maps / directories for businesses without websites |\n| **Site Building** | AI builds the site (Carrd, Framer, Webflow) |\n| **Outreach** | Sends DM or email with live preview + offer |\n| **Closing** | Handles objections, sends contract, collects payment |\n\nChris's version targeted restaurants with bad menus. You could do the same for:\n- Plumbers / HVAC / contractors with no website\n- Dentists, chiropractors, salons\n- Restaurants with bad menus (like Chris)\n- Any local service business\n\nThe key insight from that post: **you don't even need to pitch them cold**. You show them a live preview of what you built FOR THEM specifically, and they can see exactly what they'd get. Much easier to close.\n\nWant me to look up more specific setups from other people doing this?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5280,"output":673,"cacheRead":54080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60033,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777752648363,"responseId":"06458d48184cb3b5e902dc4023752dc1"}}
