{"type":"message","id":"96fa3b02","parentId":"e38e0e0a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T03:34:00.808Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to serve this on a local URL. I can use Python's built-in HTTP server or Node.js to serve it. Let me start a simple HTTP server on a port. Since the form tries to POST to localhost:18789, let me start a server that handles this.\n\nLet me use Python since it's readily available, or I can use a simple Node.js one-liner. Actually, let me serve the HTML file and have it notify me when submitted. The form tries to POST to localhost:18789 - I could either set up that listener, or just use file:// protocol and have the user copy-paste the JSON. \n\nActually the simplest approach: serve the HTML file, and when they submit, show the JSON output on screen and they can copy it to me. \n\nI'll set up a local HTTP server to serve the file and handle the form submission. I need to start an HTTP server on localhost:18789 to handle the form POST, save the submitted data to a file, and notify me via Telegram. Python should work fine for this - I'll write a simple server that accepts the form data, saves it, and sends me a message when someone submits it.","thinkingSignature":"2dc9dc16ceddd1aca724687a229e6c60d9e67fe654a52a80d89cd69527acd0c9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d35j8fgti2va_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport http.server\nimport socketserver\nimport json\nimport os\nimport urllib.parse\nimport cgi\n\nPORT = 18789\nSAVE_FILE = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace-x/onboarding-responses.json\")\n\nclass Handler(http.server.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler):\n    def do_POST(self):\n        if self.path == \"/submit\":\n            content_length = int(self.headers.get(\"Content-Length\", 0))\n            body = self.rfile.read(content_length).decode(\"utf-8\")\n            data = urllib.parse.parse_qs(body) if not self.headers.get(\"Content-Type\", \"\").startswith(\"application/json\") else json.loads(body)\n            \n            # Convert to regular dict\n            if isinstance(data, dict):\n                flat = {}\n                for k, v in data.items():\n                    flat[k] = v[0] if isinstance(v, list) and len(v) == 1 else v\n                data = flat\n            \n            # Save to file\n            with open(SAVE_FILE, \"w\") as f:\n                json.dump(data, f, indent=2)\n            \n            self.send_response(200)\n            self.send_header(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n            self.end_headers()\n            self.wfile.write(json.dumps({\"ok\": True}).encode())\n            return\n        \n        # Serve static files for /\n        if self.path == \"/\":\n            self.path = \"/onboarding-form/index.html\"\n        return super().do_POST()\n\n    def log_message(self, format, *args):\n        pass  # quiet logs\n\nos.chdir(os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace-x\"))\nwith socketserver.TCPServer((\"\", PORT), Handler) as httpd:\n    print(f\"Serving on http://localhost:{PORT}\")\n    httpd.serve_forever()\n","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/serve-form.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3096,"output":664,"cacheRead":57184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60944,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777779234019,"responseId":"0645f52244ef3f485ad7f55bd8d3c47f"}}
