{"type":"message","id":"59c5be42","parentId":"c5ef3600","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:08:29.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - I have:\n1. `yt-dlp` installed for downloading videos\n2. `whisper` installed for transcription\n3. Whisper models cached: small.pt, small.en.pt, medium.pt, base.pt, large-v3-turbo.pt\n\nNow I need to write a script that:\n1. Finds liked posts with videos\n2. Downloads the video (or audio only)\n3. Transcribes it with whisper\n4. Saves transcript + summary to a file\n5. Deletes the video to save storage\n6. Stores this in the x-data folder\n\nLet me write this script and save the video processing as a capability. I should also update the analyze-likes script to handle videos.\n\n\nBuilding the video processing pipeline...\n","thinkingSignature":"c06bb08e516dcbdc5a70459586562580ed6b2e2343b2dc441854d0ea7f913b59"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood — `yt-dlp` and `whisper` are both installed. Let me write the script that handles the full pipeline:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jbm86196ykpj_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Transcribe X video posts from likes\n# Usage: bash transcribe-video.sh <tweet_id> <video_url>\n\nTWEET_ID=\"$1\"\nVIDEO_URL=\"$2\"\nOUTPUT_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data/video-transcripts\"\nTEMP_DIR=\"/tmp/x-video-transcribe\"\n\nmkdir -p \"$OUTPUT_DIR\"\nmkdir -p \"$TEMP_DIR\"\n\nif [ -z \"$TWEET_ID\" ] || [ -z \"$VIDEO_URL\" ]; then\n    echo \"Usage: transcribe-video.sh <tweet_id> <video_url>\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check if already transcribed\nOUTPUT_FILE=\"$OUTPUT_DIR/${TWEET_ID}.json\"\nif [ -f \"$OUTPUT_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Already transcribed: $TWEET_ID\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\necho \"Processing: $TWEET_ID\"\necho \"URL: $VIDEO_URL\"\n\n# Download audio only (faster, less storage)\nAUDIO_FILE=\"$TEMP_DIR/${TWEET_ID}.m4a\"\nyt-dlp -x --audio-format m4a --audio-quality 0 -o \"$AUDIO_FILE\" \"$VIDEO_URL\" > /dev/null 2>&1\n\nif [ ! -f \"$AUDIO_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Failed to download: $VIDEO_URL\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\nFILE_SIZE=$(stat -f%z \"$AUDIO_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || stat -c%s \"$AUDIO_FILE\" 2>/dev/null)\nif [ \"$FILE_SIZE\" -lt 1000 ]; then\n    echo \"Download too small, likely failed: $AUDIO_FILE\"\n    rm -f \"$AUDIO_FILE\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"Downloaded: $(du -h \"$AUDIO_FILE\" | cut -f1)\"\necho \"Transcribing...\"\n\n# Transcribe\nTRANSCRIPT_FILE=\"$TEMP_DIR/${TWEET_ID}.txt\"\nwhisper \"$AUDIO_FILE\" \\\n    --model medium \\\n    --output_dir \"$TEMP_DIR\" \\\n    --output_format txt \\\n    --language English \\\n    > /dev/null 2>&1\n\nif [ ! -f \"$TRANSCRIPT_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Transcription failed for: $TWEET_ID\"\n    rm -f \"$AUDIO_FILE\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Read transcript\nTRANSCRIPT=$(cat \"$TRANSCRIPT_FILE\")\nTRANSCRIPT_LEN=${#TRANSCRIPT}\n\nif [ \"$TRANSCRIPT_LEN\" -lt 20 ]; then\n    echo \"Transcript too short, likely failed: $TWEET_ID\"\n    rm -f \"$AUDIO_FILE\" \"$TRANSCRIPT_FILE\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Build summary\nSUMMARY=$(echo \"$TRANSCRIPT\" | python3 -c \"\nimport sys\ntext = sys.stdin.read()\n# Simple summary: first 300 chars + key phrases\nsummary = text[:300].strip()\nif len(text) > 300:\n    summary += '...'\n# Add some context about length\nwords = len(text.split())\nsummary += f'\\n\\n[Full transcript: {words} words, ~{len(text)} chars]'\nprint(summary)\n\")\n\n# Save JSON\npython3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\n\ndata = {\n    'tweet_id': '$TWEET_ID',\n    'video_url': '$VIDEO_URL',\n    'transcript': '''$TRANSCRIPT''',\n    'summary': '''$SUMMARY''',\n    'word_count': len('''$TRANSCRIPT'''.split()),\n    'transcribed_at': '2026-05-03'\n}\n\nwith open('$OUTPUT_FILE', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(data, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint('Saved:', '$OUTPUT_FILE')\n\"\n\n# Clean up temp files\nrm -f \"$AUDIO_FILE\" \"$TRANSCRIPT_FILE\"\n\necho \"Done! Transcript: $OUTPUT_FILE\"\necho \"---\"\necho \"$SUMMARY\"","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-scripts/transcribe-video.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1137,"output":1069,"cacheRead":75776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781283399,"responseId":"0645fd2a623d3a88fc1b916d8724c1c2"}}
