{"type":"message","id":"59ee7e26","parentId":"ee2f26db","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:09:19.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The likes data from the X API v2 doesn't include media entities. The full tweet data with media would need to be fetched separately using the `/2/tweets` endpoint with `tweet.fields=entities,media` or by fetching individual tweets. \n\nThe issue is that the liked tweets endpoint only returns basic tweet fields by default. I'd need to:\n1. Fetch each tweet individually with `tweet.fields=entities,media`\n2. Or use the browser to look at the likes page\n\nFor now, let me update the script to do proper fetching with media fields. But let me also think about a smarter approach - since the API doesn't return media, I should use the browser approach to scan the actual likes page.\n \nI think the better path forward is to write a script that fetches individual tweets directly from the API with the right parameters to include media data. Let me create an updated script that does this.\n","thinkingSignature":"89ce11e2a886c746ef8a4c0c313f075f003eb56085bfdf29e5b9d0e3a686dcd5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kgf5kzqgdnhj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl /2/tweets/2050168915020361785?tweet.fields=entities,media 2>&1 | head -50","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":454,"output":249,"cacheRead":79424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80127,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781353323,"responseId":"0645fd69f00df0f17787cbaa49493193"}}
