{"type":"message","id":"7af64563","parentId":"11ad7dfb","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:09:38.195Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The X API v2 doesn't support `media` as a `tweet.fields` parameter. But the tweet objects from the likes endpoint only returned `id`, `text`, and `edit_history_tweet_ids` - no entities, no media. The media data is missing from the API response we got.\n\nLet me try using the browser to look at the tweets with videos. Actually, let me just check the includes data from the likes response, since the X API typically returns includes.media separately.\n\nActually, looking back at the likes response, it was truncated. The full response might have included `includes`. Let me check the saved file more carefully.\n\nWait, I saved all the tweets but the API response only included `id`, `text`, `edit_history_tweet_ids`. \n\nThe full tweet objects with media and entities were only in the first API call before I paginated through the rest. So the simplest fix is to just re-fetch the full tweet objects using the IDs I collected, requesting the entities field explicitly.\n","thinkingSignature":"d127b45882f2e778c98564097249f059ba7b47a58b2d447ca5291040f11662ce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rkhz635e89ol_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl \"/2/tweets/2050168915020361785?tweet.fields=entities,created_at,public_metrics&expansions=entities.media.media_keys&media.fields=type,url,preview_image_url,video_duration_ms\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(json.dumps(d, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:2000])\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":399,"output":330,"cacheRead":79872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781369527,"responseId":"0645fd79b9702f2515e6755cba884bf5"}}
