{"type":"message","id":"5482ee22","parentId":"4dc3dcb8","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:10:57.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the tweet text doesn't directly contain \"x.com\" for all video tweets. The `get_video_tweets` function looks for \"x.com\" and \"/video/\" in the text, but many tweets have URLs like \"https://t.co/XXXXX\" which are shortened URLs.\n\nThe real approach is: look at the `public_metrics` or entities from the likes data. But the API data from the likes endpoint doesn't include media info.\n\nSo the approach has to be:\n1. Take each liked tweet ID\n2. Re-fetch it with the media expansions parameter to get media info\n3. Check if it has a video\n4. If yes, download + transcribe\n\nLet me update the script to fetch each tweet individually with media expansions. This will be slow (1 API call per tweet) but accurate.\n\n\nBut with 1132 tweets, that's a lot of API calls. I should instead look for tweets that contain t.co URLs since those are usually video links on X. The issue is that the likes JSON data I saved doesn't include entity info, but when I check a specific tweet ID directly like `2050011880886784235`, the API does return video info if I use the right expansions.\n\nSo my best approach is to filter the likes data for tweets with t.co URLs pointing to X, then re-fetch those specific tweet IDs with media expansions to check for actual video content.\n","thinkingSignature":"0554dc40923f2262ae8c271598a8bbd9f75d8606e0ef0ca010b3a5ee0c256082"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ia5bkqwcl0zh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json, os\n\nDATA_DIR = os.path.expanduser('~/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data')\nwith open(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'all-likes.json')) as f:\n    likes = json.load(f)\n\n# Find tweets with t.co URLs pointing to X video pages\nvideo_tweet_ids = []\nfor tweet in likes:\n    tid = tweet.get('id','')\n    text = tweet.get('text','')\n    # Look for t.co URLs in tweet that are X video links\n    if 't.co' in text:\n        # Check the expanded_url in entities if available\n        entities = tweet.get('entities', {})\n        for url_info in entities.get('urls', []):\n            expanded = url_info.get('expanded_url', '')\n            if 'x.com' in expanded and ('/video/' in expanded or 'pic.x.com' in expanded):\n                video_tweet_ids.append(tid)\n                break\n\nprint(f'Tweets with X video URLs: {len(video_tweet_ids)}')\nprint(f'IDs: {video_tweet_ids[:20]}')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":225,"output":555,"cacheRead":84224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781442718,"responseId":"0645fdc272f738ab6ee0fcb2a0af1fc6"}}
