{"type":"message","id":"636fb836","parentId":"bbf0c52e","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:11:09.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The likes data we collected doesn't have the full entities data. The API response only returned minimal data (text, id, edit_history_tweet_ids). We need to re-fetch the tweets with media expansions. Let me modify the approach to re-fetch tweets from the full data we already have (the tweet IDs) and fetch their media data separately.\n\nActually wait - from the earlier API call to get tweet 2050011880886784235, we got full media info. So we CAN get media info via the API. The issue is that our collected likes data doesn't include entities/expanded_urls. \n\nLet me take a different approach - let's just use the browser to go through the tweets with videos. Or better yet, let me re-think this.\n\n\nI could iterate through all the like IDs and query the API individually for each one with media expansions, but that's 1132 API calls and we'd hit rate limits. The browser approach might work better - I could use it to scroll through your likes and find the videos there.\n","thinkingSignature":"2c6fac851d933e0abd89a302c93b7e068388348271c9dca7aad228d234de0793"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe likes data I collected doesn't include media URLs — the API only gave me basic tweet info. I need to re-fetch each tweet to get the video URLs, but doing that for 1,132 tweets would hit rate limits fast.\n\nHere's the plan — two options:\n\n**Option A: Browser-based (slow but free)**\nI use the browser to go through your likes page, find videos, download and transcribe them. Takes a while but doesn't hit API limits.\n\n**Option B: Process in batches via API**\nI re-fetch tweets in batches with media expansion, find the ones with videos, then process those. Faster but uses API calls.\n\n**Option C: Use the X API properly**\nThe `liked_tweets` endpoint should support `tweet.fields` parameter. Let me try fetching all your likes again but with media fields this time.\n\nWant me to try Option B or C first? Or just go with the browser if you want to avoid API usage?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":389,"output":407,"cacheRead":84352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777781457714,"responseId":"0645fdd11d29936cb02f991863816983"}}
