{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"393\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-05-03 00:15 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"6eb850ae","parentId":"eb0e5eca","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:16:04.797Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"ec771d10","parentId":"6eb850ae","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:16:41.510Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants:\n1. Daily scan of both likes AND bookmarks\n2. Only announce/report if there are NEW ones\n3. If no new ones, do nothing (no announcement needed)\n\nSo I need to set up:\n1. A script that:\n   - Checks for NEW likes since last checkpoint\n   - Checks for NEW bookmarks since last checkpoint  \n   - If either has new content, process it (transcribe videos, etc.) and report findings\n   \n2. A cron job that runs every 24hrs (or every few hours) to do this check\n\nLet me also figure out the browser approach for bookmarks since the xurl bookmarks endpoint doesn't work with OAuth 1.0a.\n\n\nI should write a script that handles the full daily check and report workflow, then set up a cron job to run it. The script will check for new likes and bookmarks since the last run, and only send a report if there's actual new content to share.\n\nWriting the daily check script... I should just ask Bobby for clarification on the timing rather than continuing to debate this.\n","thinkingSignature":"20c1b8ebd3270772ddd429cb793cd54718ccea85de3beb0d38f44564ad672852"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nPerfect. So the workflow is:\n\n- **Daily scan:** Check for new likes + bookmarks since last run\n- **If new content found:** Process it (videos, engagement, content themes) and report what I found\n- **If nothing new:** Do nothing, no announcement needed\n\nLet me set up the script + cron job now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0ycx5lub3d0z_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily X scan for Bobby — checks new likes and bookmarks.\nOnly reports if new content found.\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\n# Paths\nHOME = os.path.expanduser(\"~\")\nDATA_DIR = f\"{HOME}/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data\"\nCHECKPOINT_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-scan-checkpoint.json\"\nLIKES_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/all-likes.json\"\nPROCESSED_LIKES_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/processed-like-ids.json\"\nPROCESSED_BOOKMARKS_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/processed-bookmark-ids.json\"\n\nos.makedirs(DATA_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\ndef load_checkpoint():\n    if os.path.exists(CHECKPOINT_FILE):\n        with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\n        \"last_like_id\": None,\n        \"last_bookmark_id\": None,\n        \"last_scan_date\": None\n    }\n\ndef save_checkpoint(cp):\n    with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(cp, f, indent=2)\n\ndef get_all_likes_via_api():\n    \"\"\"Fetch all likes using xurl with pagination.\"\"\"\n    print(\"Fetching likes...\")\n    all_likes = []\n    token = \"\"\n    while True:\n        if token:\n            result = subprocess.run(\n                ['xurl', f'/2/users/1959983838211260416/liked_tweets?pagination_token={token}'],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=20\n            )\n        else:\n            result = subprocess.run(\n                ['xurl', '/2/users/1959983838211260416/liked_tweets'],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=20\n            )\n        \n        if result.returncode != 0:\n            print(f\"  xurl error: {result.stderr[:100]}\")\n            break\n        \n        try:\n            d = json.loads(result.stdout)\n        except:\n            print(f\"  JSON parse error\")\n            break\n        \n        data = d.get('data', [])\n        if not data:\n            break\n        \n        all_likes.extend(data)\n        meta = d.get('meta', {})\n        token = meta.get('next_token', '')\n        if not token:\n            break\n    \n    # Save all likes\n    with open(LIKES_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(all_likes, f, indent=2)\n    \n    print(f\"  Fetched {len(all_likes)} likes\")\n    return all_likes\n\ndef get_all_bookmarks_via_browser():\n    \"\"\"Get new bookmarks by comparing browser page to saved list.\"\"\"\n    # Use the already-saved bookmark IDs if any\n    bookmarks_file = f\"{DATA_DIR}/all-bookmarks.json\"\n    old_bookmarks = set()\n    if os.path.exists(bookmarks_file):\n        with open(bookmarks_file) as f:\n            old_bookmarks = set(json.load(f))\n    \n    # Navigate to bookmarks page and get what's there now\n    # For now, return empty list if no new way to fetch\n    return [], old_bookmarks\n\ndef get_new_items(all_items, processed_file, last_id_key):\n    \"\"\"Find items newer than last processed.\"\"\"\n    processed = set()\n    if os.path.exists(processed_file):\n        with open(processed_file) as f:\n            processed = set(json.load(f))\n    \n    new_items = [item for item in all_items if item.get('id') not in processed]\n    \n    if all_items:\n        latest_id = all_items[0].get('id') if all_items else None\n    \n    return new_items, processed\n\ndef find_video_tweets(tweets):\n    \"\"\"Filter tweets that have videos in them.\"\"\"\n    video_tweets = []\n    for tweet in tweets:\n        tid = tweet.get('id', '')\n        text = tweet.get('text', '')\n        # Look for X video URLs\n        if 'x.com/' in text and ('/video/' in text or 'pic.x.com' in text):\n            video_tweets.append(tid)\n    return video_tweets\n\ndef transcribe_tweet_video(tid, tweet_url, original_text):\n    \"\"\"Download and transcribe a tweet video.\"\"\"\n    temp_audio = f\"/tmp/x-daily-{tid}.m4a\"\n    transcript_file = f\"{HOME}/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data/video-transcripts/{tid}.json\"\n    \n    # Skip if already transcribed\n    if os.path.exists(transcript_file):\n        return None\n    \n    # Download video\n    dl_cmd = [\n        'yt-dlp', '-x', '--audio-format', 'm4a',\n        '--audio-quality', '0', '-o', temp_audio,\n        '--quiet', '--no-playlist',\n        tweet_url\n    ]\n    result = subprocess.run(dl_cmd, capture_output=True, timeout=120)\n    \n    if result.returncode != 0 or not os.path.exists(temp_audio):\n        return None\n    \n    size = os.path.getsize(temp_audio)\n    if size < 5000:\n        os.remove(temp_audio)\n        return None\n    \n    # Transcribe\n    tr_cmd = [\n        'whisper', temp_audio,\n        '--model', 'medium',\n        '--output_dir', '/tmp',\n        '--output_format', 'txt',\n        '--language', 'English',\n        '--verbose', 'False'\n    ]\n    result = subprocess.run(tr_cmd, capture_output=True, timeout=300)\n    \n    # Find output\n    txt_file = temp_audio.replace('.m4a', '.txt')\n    transcript = None\n    if os.path.exists(txt_file):\n        with open(txt_file, 'r', errors='ignore') as f:\n            transcript = f.read().strip()\n    \n    if not transcript or len(transcript) < 20:\n        if os.path.exists(temp_audio): os.remove(temp_audio)\n        if txt_file and os.path.exists(txt_file): os.remove(txt_file)\n        return None\n    \n    words = len(transcript.split())\n    summary = transcript[:400].strip()\n    if len(transcript) > 400:\n        summary += '...'\n    summary += f\"\\n\\n[{words} words]\"\n    \n    # Save\n    data = {\n        'tweet_id': tid,\n        'video_url': tweet_url,\n        'original_text': original_text,\n        'transcript': transcript,\n        'summary': summary,\n        'word_count': words,\n        'transcribed_at': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n    }\n    \n    with open(transcript_file, 'w', errors='ignore') as f:\n        json.dump(data, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n    \n    # Cleanup\n    os.remove(temp_audio)\n    if os.path.exists(txt_file): os.remove(txt_file)\n    \n    return summary\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"\\n=== X Daily Scan: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')} ===\\n\")\n    \n    checkpoint = load_checkpoint()\n    cp_like_id = checkpoint.get('last_like_id')\n    cp_bookmark_id = checkpoint.get('last_bookmark_id')\n    \n    # Fetch all likes\n    all_likes = get_all_likes_via_api()\n    \n    if not all_likes:\n        print(\"No likes fetched, exiting\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    # Find new likes\n    new_likes = []\n    if cp_like_id:\n        for i, tweet in enumerate(all_likes):\n            if tweet.get('id') == cp_like_id:\n                new_likes = all_likes[:i]\n                break\n        if not new_likes and all_likes[0].get('id') != cp_like_id:\n            new_likes = all_likes  # ID not found, assume all are new\n    else:\n        new_likes = all_likes  # First run, all are new\n    \n    print(f\"New likes since last scan: {len(new_likes)}\")\n    \n    # Find video tweets\n    video_tweet_ids = find_video_tweets(new_likes)\n    print(f\"New likes with videos: {len(video_tweet_ids)}\")\n    \n    # For bookmarks - we'll check via browser since API doesn't support OAuth1\n    # For now just report on likes\n    new_bookmarks = []  # Will be populated via browser check\n    \n    # Save processed like IDs\n    with open(PROCESSED_LIKES_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump([t['id'] for t in all_likes], f, indent=2)\n    \n    # Update checkpoint\n    checkpoint['last_like_id'] = all_likes[0].get('id') if all_likes else cp_like_id\n    checkpoint['last_bookmark_id'] = cp_bookmark_id  # Will be updated when bookmarks work\n    checkpoint['last_scan_date'] = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n    save_checkpoint(checkpoint)\n    \n    # Report if new content\n    has_new = len(new_likes) > 0 or len(new_bookmarks) > 0\n    \n    if not has_new:\n        print(\"No new content. Exiting silently.\")\n        sys.exit(0)\n    \n    # Process video tweets\n    transcripts = []\n    for tweet in new_likes:\n        tid = tweet.get('id', '')\n        if tid in video_tweet_ids:\n            tweet_url = f\"https://x.com/i/status/{tid}\"\n            original_text = tweet.get('text', '')[:100]\n            result = transcribe_tweet_video(tid, tweet_url, original_text)\n            if result:\n                transcripts.append({\n                    'tweet_id': tid,\n                    'summary': result,\n                    'text': original_text\n                })\n    \n    # Build report\n    report = f\"New X content found ({len(new_likes)} new likes):\\n\\n\"\n    \n    if video_tweet_ids:\n        report += f\"Videos found: {len(video_tweet_ids)}\\n\"\n        for t in transcripts:\n            report += f\"\\n- {t['text'][:80]}...\\n  {t['summary'][:150]}...\\n\"\n    \n    if not video_tweet_ids:\n        report += \"No videos in new likes.\\n\"\n    \n    report += f\"\\nScanned: {datetime.now().strftime('%H:%M')}\"\n    \n    print(f\"\\n{report}\")\n    \n    # Save report\n    report_file = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-daily-report-latest.json\"\n    with open(report_file, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump({\n            'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            'new_likes_count': len(new_likes),\n            'new_video_count': len(video_tweet_ids),\n            'transcripts': transcripts,\n            'report': report\n        }, f, indent=2)\n    \n    print(f\"\\nReport saved to {report_file}\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-scripts/daily-x-scan.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92483,"output":2649,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95260,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781764797,"responseId":"0645ff05a9c3d5e0364df3465b4997a5"}}
