{"type":"message","id":"15480df1","parentId":"a1bf6075","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:17:00.756Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me set up the 24-hour cron job to run daily. The cron should:- Run the daily scan script- If new content found, report to Bobby via Telegram- If no new content, stay silent\n\nI need to set up a cron that:\n1. Runs the scan script\n2. If it finds new content, delivers the report to Bobby via Telegram\n3. If no new content, sends nothing\n\nFor the cron, I'll use an agentTurn in an isolated session, which will handle the logic and send results to Telegram if there are new findings.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The cron should:\n- Run the scan\n\n\n- Only message Bobby if there's new content found, otherwise remain silent per his preference\n\nI'll set up a cron job that triggers an isolated agent session to run the scan, and the agent can decide whether to send a Telegram message based on what it finds.\n","thinkingSignature":"74c32479dc060c1927a91a79636a656fdfe9c0cbe6213958a004ac55e724baf8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNow let me set up the 24-hour cron job:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3lr5cgh7hias_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily X scan — runs silently, only reports if new video likes are found.\nSaves transcripts to x-data/video-transcripts/\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nHOME = os.path.expanduser(\"~\")\nDATA_DIR = f\"{HOME}/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data\"\nCHECKPOINT_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-scan-checkpoint.json\"\nPROCESSED_LIKES_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/processed-like-ids.json\"\n\nos.makedirs(DATA_DIR, exist_ok=True)\nos.makedirs(f\"{DATA_DIR}/video-transcripts\", exist_ok=True)\n\ndef load_checkpoint():\n    if os.path.exists(CHECKPOINT_FILE):\n        with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\"last_like_id\": None, \"last_scan_date\": None}\n\ndef save_checkpoint(cp):\n    with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(cp, f, indent=2)\n\ndef fetch_all_likes():\n    all_likes = []\n    token = \"\"\n    while True:\n        cmd = ['xurl', f'/2/users/1959983838211260416/liked_tweets{\"?pagination_token=\"+token if token else \"\"}']\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=20)\n        if result.returncode != 0:\n            break\n        try:\n            d = json.loads(result.stdout)\n        except:\n            break\n        data = d.get('data', [])\n        if not data:\n            break\n        all_likes.extend(data)\n        token = d.get('meta', {}).get('next_token', '')\n        if not token:\n            break\n    return all_likes\n\ndef has_video_in_text(text):\n    return 'x.com/' in text and ('/video/' in text or 'pic.x.com' in text)\n\ndef transcribe_video(tid, tweet_url):\n    transcript_file = f\"{DATA_DIR}/video-transcripts/{tid}.json\"\n    if os.path.exists(transcript_file):\n        return None  # already done\n    \n    temp_audio = f\"/tmp/x-scan-{tid}.m4a\"\n    dl = subprocess.run([\n        'yt-dlp', '-x', '--audio-format', 'm4a', '--audio-quality', '0',\n        '-o', temp_audio, '--quiet', '--no-playlist', tweet_url\n    ], capture_output=True, timeout=120)\n    \n    if dl.returncode != 0 or not os.path.exists(temp_audio):\n        return None\n    \n    if os.path.getsize(temp_audio) < 5000:\n        os.remove(temp_audio)\n        return None\n    \n    tr = subprocess.run([\n        'whisper', temp_audio, '--model', 'medium', '--output_dir', '/tmp',\n        '--output_format', 'txt', '--language', 'English', '--verbose', 'False'\n    ], capture_output=True, timeout=300)\n    \n    txt = temp_audio.replace('.m4a', '.txt')\n    transcript = None\n    if os.path.exists(txt):\n        with open(txt, 'r', errors='ignore') as f:\n            transcript = f.read().strip()\n    \n    for f in [temp_audio, txt]:\n        if os.path.exists(f):\n            os.remove(f)\n    \n    if not transcript or len(transcript) < 20:\n        return None\n    \n    words = len(transcript.split())\n    summary = transcript[:400].strip()\n    if len(transcript) > 400:\n        summary += '...'\n    summary += f\"\\n\\n[{words} words]\"\n    \n    with open(transcript_file, 'w', errors='ignore') as f:\n        json.dump({\n            'tweet_id': tid, 'video_url': tweet_url,\n            'transcript': transcript, 'summary': summary,\n            'word_count': words,\n            'transcribed_at': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n        }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n    \n    return summary\n\ndef main():\n    cp = load_checkpoint()\n    last_id = cp.get('last_like_id')\n    \n    all_likes = fetch_all_likes()\n    if not all_likes:\n        sys.exit(0)\n    \n    # Find new likes since last scan\n    if last_id:\n        idx = next((i for i, t in enumerate(all_likes) if t['id'] == last_id), None)\n        new_likes = all_likes[:idx] if idx else []\n    else:\n        new_likes = []  # First run — don't report everything, just set checkpoint\n    \n    if not new_likes:\n        # No new likes, just update checkpoint\n        cp['last_like_id'] = all_likes[0]['id']\n        cp['last_scan_date'] = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n        save_checkpoint(cp)\n        sys.exit(0)  # Silent exit\n    \n    # Process new likes with videos\n    video_tweets = [t for t in new_likes if has_video_in_text(t['text'])]\n    \n    results = []\n    for tweet in video_tweets:\n        tid = tweet['id']\n        url = f\"https://x.com/i/status/{tid}\"\n        summary = transcribe_video(tid, url)\n        if summary:\n            results.append({'tid': tid, 'summary': summary, 'text': tweet['text'][:80]})\n        time.sleep(0.5)\n    \n    # Update checkpoint\n    cp['last_like_id'] = all_likes[0]['id']\n    cp['last_scan_date'] = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n    save_checkpoint(cp)\n    \n    # Save processed IDs\n    with open(PROCESSED_LIKES_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump([t['id'] for t in all_likes], f)\n    \n    # Build output for agent to report\n    output = {\n        'new_likes_count': len(new_likes),\n        'new_videos': results,\n        'has_new': len(results) > 0\n    }\n    \n    out_file = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-daily-output.json\"\n    with open(out_file, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(output, f, indent=2)\n    \n    print(json.dumps(output))\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-scripts/daily-x-scan.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2472,"output":1602,"cacheRead":92544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96618,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781801917,"responseId":"0645ff2a9025cb5224e4dec9f26a30d0"}}
