:"You are Agent X. Run the daily X scan.\n\nExecute: python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-scripts/daily-x-scan.py\n\nRead the output file at ~/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data/x-daily-output.json\n\nIF has_new is true:\n- Report to Bobby on Telegram: \"Found [N] new video posts in your likes. Here's what they contain: [summaries]\"\n- Include the full report\n\nIF has_new is false:\n- Do NOT announce anything to Bobby. Just exit silently.\n- The scan completed successfully with no new video likes.\n\nAlso check ~/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data/x-scan-checkpoint.json to confirm the scan ran.\n\nDo NOT send any message if there are no new videos.","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8212808444"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1777813200000}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777781828552}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd6be509","parentId":"91ba4c2a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:17:35.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron job is set up. Now let me also do the browser-based bookmark check. The daily scan currently only handles likes via API (since bookmarks don't work with OAuth1). I need to set up a browser-based bookmark scanner too.\n\nActually, let me first test the daily scan script to make sure it works, then set up the bookmark part.\n\nFor bookmarks, I'll need a separate browser-based approach since the API doesn't support OAuth1 for bookmarks.\n\nLet me also write a bookmark scanner that uses the browser. But that would require the browser to be open and logged in. That's not ideal for a cron job.\n\nActually, I should just tell Bobby that bookmarks will need a different approach since the X API doesn't support OAuth1 for the bookmarks endpoint, and I'll figure out a way to handle it.\n\n\nI think the practical solution is to run a daily browser-based bookmark check on-demand or whenever the browser is available, then focus on getting the like scanning and video processing working properly first. The full setup will involve the script for finding videos, a transcription process, and then the cron job to tie it together. I'll handle the full initial scan of the existing 1,176 likes to find and process any video content, and set up the 24-hour cron job to keep things updated going forward.\n","thinkingSignature":"e38d9a2bee2a3df8df73e8f9c5d0530eba1c02e9d354889e9437b70162198641"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCron job is set. Now let me run the full scan of all your likes to get the initial video context. This will take a bit since I'm going through 1,132 posts and transcribing any videos I find.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n07fokerkqq4_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nInitial full scan of all likes — find videos, transcribe, set checkpoint.\nThis runs once to build the initial database.\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nHOME = os.path.expanduser(\"~\")\nDATA_DIR = f\"{HOME}/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-data\"\nTRANSCRIPT_DIR = f\"{DATA_DIR}/video-transcripts\"\nCHECKPOINT_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-scan-checkpoint.json\"\nPROCESSED_LIKES_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/processed-like-ids.json\"\nOUTPUT_FILE = f\"{DATA_DIR}/x-daily-output.json\"\n\nos.makedirs(TRANSCRIPT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\ndef load_checkpoint():\n    if os.path.exists(CHECKPOINT_FILE):\n        with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\"last_like_id\": None, \"last_scan_date\": None}\n\ndef save_checkpoint(cp):\n    with open(CHECKPOINT_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(cp, f, indent=2)\n\ndef fetch_all_likes():\n    all_likes = []\n    token = \"\"\n    print(\"Fetching all likes from API...\")\n    while True:\n        if token:\n            cmd = ['xurl', f'/2/users/1959983838211260416/liked_tweets?pagination_token={token}']\n        else:\n            cmd = ['xurl', '/2/users/1959983838211260416/liked_tweets']\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=20)\n        if result.returncode != 0:\n            print(f\"  Error: {result.stderr[:100]}\")\n            break\n        try:\n            d = json.loads(result.stdout)\n        except:\n            break\n        data = d.get('data', [])\n        if not data:\n            break\n        all_likes.extend(data)\n        print(f\"  Fetched {len(all_likes)}...\")\n        token = d.get('meta', {}).get('next_token', '')\n        if not token:\n            break\n    return all_likes\n\ndef has_video_in_text(text):\n    return 'x.com/' in text and ('/video/' in text or 'pic.x.com' in text)\n\ndef transcribe_video(tid, tweet_url, original_text):\n    transcript_file = f\"{TRANSCRIPT_DIR}/{tid}.json\"\n    if os.path.exists(transcript_file):\n        with open(transcript_file) as f:\n            d = json.load(f)\n        return {'tid': tid, 'summary': d.get('summary',''), 'text': original_text[:80], 'status': 'already_done'}\n    \n    temp_audio = f\"/tmp/x-full-{tid}.m4a\"\n    dl = subprocess.run([\n        'yt-dlp', '-x', '--audio-format', 'm4a', '--audio-quality', '0',\n        '-o', temp_audio, '--quiet', '--no-playlist', tweet_url\n    ], capture_output=True, timeout=120)\n    \n    if dl.returncode != 0 or not os.path.exists(temp_audio):\n        return {'tid': tid, 'summary': None, 'text': original_text[:80], 'status': 'download_failed'}\n    \n    size = os.path.getsize(temp_audio)\n    if size < 5000:\n        os.remove(temp_audio)\n        return {'tid': tid, 'summary': None, 'text': original_text[:80], 'status': 'file_too_small'}\n    \n    print(f\"    Transcribing {tid} ({size/1024:.0f}KB)...\")\n    tr = subprocess.run([\n        'whisper', temp_audio, '--model', 'medium', '--output_dir', '/tmp',\n        '--output_format', 'txt', '--language', 'English', '--verbose', 'False'\n    ], capture_output=True, timeout=300)\n    \n    txt = temp_audio.replace('.m4a', '.txt')\n    transcript = None\n    if os.path.exists(txt):\n        with open(txt, 'r', errors='ignore') as f:\n            transcript = f.read().strip()\n    \n    for f in [temp_audio, txt]:\n        if os.path.exists(f):\n            os.remove(f)\n    \n    if not transcript or len(transcript) < 20:\n        return {'tid': tid, 'summary': None, 'text': original_text[:80], 'status': 'transcribe_failed'}\n    \n    words = len(transcript.split())\n    summary = transcript[:400].strip()\n    if len(transcript) > 400:\n        summary += '...'\n    summary += f\"\\n\\n[{words} words]\"\n    \n    with open(transcript_file, 'w', errors='ignore') as f:\n        json.dump({\n            'tweet_id': tid,\n            'video_url': tweet_url,\n            'original_text': original_text,\n            'transcript': transcript,\n            'summary': summary,\n            'word_count': words,\n            'transcribed_at': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n        }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n    \n    return {'tid': tid, 'summary': summary, 'text': original_text[:80], 'status': 'done'}\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"\\n=== Full X Likes Scan: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')} ===\\n\")\n    \n    all_likes = fetch_all_likes()\n    if not all_likes:\n        print(\"No likes fetched\")\n        return\n    \n    print(f\"\\nTotal likes: {len(all_likes)}\")\n    \n    # Save all likes\n    with open(f\"{DATA_DIR}/all-likes.json\", 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(all_likes, f, indent=2)\n    \n    # Save processed IDs\n    with open(PROCESSED_LIKES_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump([t['id'] for t in all_likes], f)\n    \n    # Find all video tweets\n    video_tweets = [t for t in all_likes if has_video_in_text(t['text'])]\n    print(f\"Video tweets found: {len(video_tweets)}\")\n    \n    # Set checkpoint\n    cp = load_checkpoint()\n    cp['last_like_id'] = all_likes[0]['id']\n    cp['last_scan_date'] = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n    save_checkpoint(cp)\n    \n    if not video_tweets:\n        print(\"No videos found. Setting up for daily scan.\")\n        output = {'new_likes_count': 0, 'new_videos': [], 'has_new': False}\n        with open(OUTPUT_FILE, 'w') as f:\n            json.dump(output, f, indent=2)\n        return\n    \n    # Process each video\n    results = []\n    already_done = 0\n    downloaded = 0\n    errors = 0\n    \n    print(f\"\\nProcessing {len(video_tweets)} videos...\\n\")\n    \n    for i, tweet in enumerate(video_tweets):\n        tid = tweet['id']\n        url = f\"https://x.com/i/status/{tid}\"\n        original_text = tweet['text']\n        \n        print(f\"[{i+1}/{len(video_tweets)}] {tid}\")\n        \n        result = transcribe_video(tid, url, original_text)\n        \n        if result['status'] == 'already_done':\n            already_done += 1\n            print(f\"  Already done\")\n        elif result['status'] == 'done':\n            downloaded += 1\n            results.append(result)\n            print(f\"  ✓ {result['summary'][:60]}...\")\n        else:\n            errors += 1\n            print(f\"  ✗ {result['status']}\")\n        \n        time.sleep(1)  # Be nice to API/disk\n    \n    # Build output\n    output = {\n        'timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M'),\n        'total_likes': len(all_likes),\n        'total_videos_found': len(video_tweets),\n        'new_videos_transcribed': downloaded,\n        'already_transcribed': already_done,\n        'errors': errors,\n        'new_videos': results,\n        'has_new': len(results) > 0\n    }\n    \n    with open(OUTPUT_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(output, f, indent=2)\n    \n    print(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\n    print(f\"Done!\")\n    print(f\"  Videos found: {len(video_tweets)}\")\n    print(f\"  Newly transcribed: {downloaded}\")\n    print(f\"  Already done: {already_done}\")\n    print(f\"  Errors: {errors}\")\n    print(f\"  Checkpoint set: {cp['last_like_id']}\")\n    print(f\"\\nOutput: {OUTPUT_FILE}\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x-scripts/full-likes-scan.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":783,"output":2238,"cacheRead":96384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99405,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781828555,"responseId":"0645ff441a4c1d25e8832cfbb29a995d"}}
