{"type":"message","id":"286f3640","parentId":"1c65748a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:19:04.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, I see! The URLs in the tweets are being shortened to t.co links, and they don't show the full x.com URL in the text. So I can't detect videos by searching for \"x.com/\" in the text. \n\nThe approach of trying to download and seeing if it's a video is the right one. The issue is the candidate filter was wrong.\n\nLet me just try downloading a few known tweet IDs that I know have videos (from the browser scan — these are tweets I saw on the likes page with \"Play Video\" buttons). Let me test downloading a few of those.\n","thinkingSignature":"f0f46c3e784d29f7bd8b50673416f2841f59b514c6ab83bb75e48c69092f3250"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vj1pdjsjadyv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test downloading some tweets we KNOW have videos (from browser scan)\npython3 -c \"\nimport json, subprocess, os\n\nvideo_tweet_ids = [\n    '2050168915020361785',  # davidfigeira - the \\$52k video\n    '2050011880886784235',  # marlowxbt - 14 year old roofing  \n    '2050297575819935934',  # clipping army in Telegram\n    '2049944840629072168',  # 19 year old Discord \\$80k\n    '2049584756359115099',  # 14 year old Claude website\n]\n\nfor tid in video_tweet_ids:\n    out_file = f'/tmp/test-{tid}.m4a'\n    if os.path.exists(out_file):\n        os.remove(out_file)\n    \n    result = subprocess.run([\n        'yt-dlp', '-x', '--audio-format', 'm4a', '--audio-quality', '0',\n        '-o', out_file, '--quiet', '--no-playlist', '--no-warnings',\n        f'https://x.com/i/status/{tid}'\n    ], capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=45)\n    \n    if os.path.exists(out_file):\n        size = os.path.getsize(out_file)\n        print(f'{tid}: ✓ VIDEO ({size/1024:.0f}KB)')\n        os.remove(out_file)\n    else:\n        print(f'{tid}: ✗ no video - {result.stderr[:80] if result.stderr else \\\"unknown\\\"}