{"type":"message","id":"7bde7e80","parentId":"4db70645","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:19:31.725Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The downloads work! The issue is that the likes data doesn't contain the full tweet text with URLs - the tweets are truncated. But I now know which tweets to look for based on what I saw in the browser. Let me update the full scan script to use the actual tweet IDs I know have videos from the browser snapshot, and run that first. Then set up the daily cron.\n\nLet me first run a targeted scan of the specific video tweets I can identify from the browser. Then set up the daily workflow.\n","thinkingSignature":"0101e12a9eba549dd627a585228ea8d68a8e369cf1fd7d2ac74f1e72af5fe571"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nDownloads work perfectly. The issue is the X API truncates tweet text so I can't detect video URLs from the text alone. But I can see from the browser which tweets have videos. Let me run the full scan now — it'll try downloading every X post link and transcribe anything that's a video.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e35syuhegrq0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"background":true,"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace-x && python3 x-scripts/full-likes-scan.py > /tmp/full-scan-v2.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"","yieldMs":2000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":257,"output":246,"cacheRead":108288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108791,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777781959700,"responseId":"0645ffc869856509b506372b23a0fa13"}}
