{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"System (untrusted): [2026-05-03 00:17:42 EDT] Exec completed (swift-ro, code 0) :: Full scan started in background (PID: 16550)\nSystem (untrusted): [2026-05-03 00:19:15 EDT] Exec completed (brisk-br, code 0) :: 2050168915020361785: ✓ VIDEO (329KB) 2050011880886784235: ✓ VIDEO (748KB) 2050297575819935934: ✓ VIDEO (489KB) 2049944840629072168: ✓ VIDEO (360KB) 2049584756359115099: ✓ VIDEO (7…\nSystem (untrusted): [2026-05-03 00:19:31 EDT] Exec completed (kind-can, code 0) :: PID: 16776\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"400\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-05-03 00:20 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"aef67fe5","parentId":"1281591a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:20:59.011Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"6645ea75","parentId":"aef67fe5","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:21:25.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying what the 24hr scan should look at. Let me restate my understanding:\n\n1. Every 24 hours, I check for NEW liked posts AND NEW bookmarked posts\n2. For each new post (regardless of whether it has a video):\n   - Note what the post is about\n   - If there's a video, transcribe it (download, transcribe, save summary, delete video)\n   - Report to the user if there's new content\n\nSo the 24hr scan is broader - it checks ALL new likes and bookmarks, not just video posts. The video transcription is just part of it when applicable. The key deliverable is: \"here's what's new in your likes and bookmarks\" - whether that's a post about local lead gen, a funny video, a tech thread, whatever.\n\nLet me confirm this understanding with the user and also update the script to include bookmarks.\n","thinkingSignature":"7b17d103792a6b1e118e34ce2bc7038cecfcdea7865c7cdaab5cd90c8092cd59"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes, here's the full picture of what the 24hr scan does:\n\n**Every 24hrs, I check:**\n- **New liked posts** — all of them, not just videos\n- **New bookmarked posts** — all of them, not just videos\n\n**For each new post I find:**\n1. Read what it's about\n2. If it has a video → download, transcribe, save summary, delete video\n3. Save the post content / topics discussed\n\n**Then I report to you ONLY if:**\n- There's new content found\n- I summarize what the posts are about so we can work on them or talk about them\n- If no new likes AND no new bookmarks → I do nothing, silent exit\n\nSo it's not just about videos. It's a daily digest of what caught your eye in the last 24hrs. The video transcription is extra context when relevant, but the main thing is knowing what you're engaging with so I can help you build on those interests.\n\n**One thing I need to figure out:** The bookmarks API requires a different auth method (OAuth 1 vs OAuth 2). I can get likes via API no problem, but bookmarks need a different approach. Should I:\n\nA) Check bookmarks via browser automation (slower, but works)\nB) Just focus on likes for now until we solve the bookmarks API issue\n\nOr do you want me to figure out how to get bookmarks working properly?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103554,"output":479,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104289,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777782059011,"responseId":"0646002b4cbc638ec0caf1dfe824f982"}}
