{"type":"message","id":"1d496822","parentId":"f9338acc","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:28:19.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants me to figure out how to get bookmarks working. Let me think about this.\n\nThe issue is that the X API has two auth methods:\n- OAuth 2 (app-only or user context) - this works for likes\n- OAuth 1.0a (user context) - this is required for bookmarks\n\nThe xurl CLI seems to use OAuth 2 by default. When I tried `xurl bookmarks`, it returned a 403 saying OAuth 1.0a is required.\n\nOptions to get bookmarks:\n\n1. **Try different xurl commands** - maybe there's a way to specify OAuth 1 auth, or use a different endpoint\n\n2. **Browser automation** - navigate to x.com/i/bookmarks and scrape the content\n\n\n3. **Look at xurl source** - see if there's a way to use OAuth 1 for certain endpoints\n\nLet me try a few things. The browser approach worked for checking likes, so I could do the same for bookmarks. But first let me see if xurl has any bookmark-specific auth options I might have missed.\n\nThe xurl CLI seems to be using OAuth 2.0 with user context based on the auth status I checked, but the bookmarks endpoint specifically requires OAuth 1.0a - this is a known limitation of the X API. So browser automation is probably my best bet here.\n\nLet me check what xurl auth options are available.\n","thinkingSignature":"3c438e9889e867ff1d682d931c82166b70407f3604b3f63eb1ab1a6acb16bfd6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tkcryv4is907_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl auth status 2>&1","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tkcryv4is907_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl --help 2>&1 | head -40","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109009,"output":369,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777782480090,"responseId":"064601d066e58039d4c18ea0b1437cab"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ed6dc57","parentId":"1d496822","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:28:19.877Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tkcryv4is907_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"default  [(no credentials)]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: –\n      bearer: –\n\n  my-app  [client_id: YOUR_CLI…]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: –\n      bearer: –\n\n▸ xai-prod  [client_id: 4isSQMmG…]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: ✓\n      bearer: –"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":80,"aggregated":"default  [(no credentials)]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: –\n      bearer: –\n\n  my-app  [client_id: YOUR_CLI…]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: –\n      bearer: –\n\n▸ xai-prod  [client_id: 4isSQMmG…]\n      redirect_uri: http://localhost:8080/callback  [built-in default]\n      oauth2: (none)\n      oauth1: ✓\n      bearer: –","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777782499877}}
{"type":"message","id":"f645b9b3","parentId":"7ed6dc57","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:28:19.878Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tkcryv4is907_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A command-line tool for making authenticated requests to the X API.\n\nShortcut commands (agent‑friendly):\n  xurl post \"Hello world!\"                        Post to X\n  xurl reply 1234567890 \"Nice!\"                   Reply to a post\n  xurl read 1234567890                             Read a post\n  xurl search \"golang\" -n 20                       Search posts\n  xurl whoami                                      Show your profile\n  xurl like 1234567890                             Like a post\n  xurl repost 1234567890                           Repost\n  xurl follow @user                                Follow a user\n  xurl dm @user \"Hey!\"                             Send a DM\n  xurl timeline                                    Home timeline\n  xurl mentions                                    Your mentions\n\nRaw API access (curl‑style):\n  basic requests        xurl /2/users/me\n                        xurl -X POST /2/tweets -d '{\"text\":\"Hello world!\"}'\n                        xurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" /2/tweets\n  authentication        xurl --auth oauth2 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth oauth1 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth app /2/users/me\n  media and streaming   xurl media upload path/to/video.mp4\n                        xurl /2/tweets/search/stream --auth app\n                        xurl -s /2/users/me\n\nMulti-app management:\n  xurl auth apps add my-app --client-id ... --client-secret ...\n  xurl auth apps list\n  xurl auth default                                # interactive picker\n  xurl auth default my-app                         # set by name\n  xurl --app my-app /2/users/me                    # per-request override\n\nRun 'xurl --help' to see all available commands.\n\nUsage:\n  xurl [flags] URL\n  xurl [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":141,"aggregated":"A command-line tool for making authenticated requests to the X API.\n\nShortcut commands (agent‑friendly):\n  xurl post \"Hello world!\"                        Post to X\n  xurl reply 1234567890 \"Nice!\"                   Reply to a post\n  xurl read 1234567890                             Read a post\n  xurl search \"golang\" -n 20                       Search posts\n  xurl whoami                                      Show your profile\n  xurl like 1234567890                             Like a post\n  xurl repost 1234567890                           Repost\n  xurl follow @user                                Follow a user\n  xurl dm @user \"Hey!\"                             Send a DM\n  xurl timeline                                    Home timeline\n  xurl mentions                                    Your mentions\n\nRaw API access (curl‑style):\n  basic requests        xurl /2/users/me\n                        xurl -X POST /2/tweets -d '{\"text\":\"Hello world!\"}'\n                        xurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" /2/tweets\n  authentication        xurl --auth oauth2 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth oauth1 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth app /2/users/me\n  media and streaming   xurl media upload path/to/video.mp4\n                        xurl /2/tweets/search/stream --auth app\n                        xurl -s /2/users/me\n\nMulti-app management:\n  xurl auth apps add my-app --client-id ... --client-secret ...\n  xurl auth apps list\n  xurl auth default                                # interactive picker\n  xurl auth default my-app                         # set by name\n  xurl --app my-app /2/users/me                    # per-request override\n\nRun 'xurl --help' to see all available commands.\n\nUsage:\n  xurl [flags] URL\n  xurl [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777782499877}}
{"type":"message","id":"13865cf8","parentId":"f645b9b3","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:28:24.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `xai-prod` app has OAuth1 credentials but the current auth shows oauth1 is checked but \"–\" which means no tokens. Let me check if we can use OAuth1 for bookmarks. The issue earlier was that `/2/users/:id/bookmarks` endpoint doesn't support OAuth1. But maybe we can use a different endpoint or approach.\n\nLet me check the raw API for bookmarks with OAuth1.\n","thinkingSignature":"1611589b1f7b9e8e7cd939935712df17788e85f0512907b51f14d470b4ebdf66"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_17lr44iyq7x1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl --auth oauth1 \"/2/users/1959983838211260416/bookmarks?max_results=10\" 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":646,"output":151,"cacheRead":109184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109981,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777782499880,"responseId":"064601e41c7d5ac77918873660bc21c5"}}
