{"type":"message","id":"982eb61a","parentId":"e1ede325","timestamp":"2026-05-03T04:28:35.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So bookmarks require OAuth 2. But xurl has OAuth 2 available in theory. The issue is that the current OAuth 2 token was not granted for the bookmarks scope. \n\nLet me check what scopes the current OAuth 2 token has and if I can re-authenticate to get the right scopes.\n\nActually, the xurl `xai-prod` app has oauth1 working. Let me check if there's a way to get a fresh oauth2 token that includes bookmarks scope. The user would need to re-run `xurl auth oauth2` to get a new token with the right scopes.\n\nBut the SKILL.md says \"do not pass secrets via agent/LLM context\" and auth must be done manually outside the session.\n \nI need to ask the user to re-authenticate with OAuth 2 to get the proper bookmarks scope, since the current token doesn't have access to this endpoint. Let me explain what scopes are needed and guide them through the re-authentication process.\n","thinkingSignature":"f84f109736ac0a7b115d7cd53a8a2c1f98d7b9fc35d4fbe4467879ddcd292803"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nFound the issue. Bookmarks API requires **OAuth 2** authentication, but your current token was set up with **OAuth 1** for some endpoints. OAuth 1 doesn't work for bookmarks.\n\nHere's what you need to do (one-time fix):\n\n```bash\nxurl auth default xai-prod\nxurl auth oauth2\n```\n\nThis will open a browser window asking you to authorize again. Hit approve and it should give you a fresh OAuth 2 token that includes bookmarks scope.\n\nAfter you do that, let me know and I'll verify it works and update the daily scan to include bookmarks too."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":165,"output":325,"cacheRead":109824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110314,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777782504831,"responseId":"064601e8415f80a9f6e76cf5efc4ddc2"}}
