{"type":"message","id":"46fa6b68","parentId":"b5ad33c2","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:06:10.701Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem. The xurl config has OAuth1 tokens but no OAuth2 tokens. Bobby needs to get OAuth2 authentication set up for the bookmarks endpoint to work.\n\nThe credentials Bobby shared include:\n- oauth2_access_token: pypByEFyBXhI8a9wa3NA_V66qk2cEqAG9qs2XkBRAaO\n- oauth2_refresh_token: mFyebA00Zegchu4hfYudjU0US3303XMbWX_wNsy9OJ\n\nThe issue is that xurl doesn't seem to support manually setting OAuth2 tokens directly - it needs to do the OAuth2 flow (opening a browser). But Bobby said \"it says something went wrong\" when trying the oauth2 flow.\n\n\nI could try configuring OAuth2 authentication with the client credentials Bobby has, but I'm not sure if xurl supports that approach. Looking at the xurl source or documentation might help, though I don't have access to those. Alternatively, I could explore using the Twitter API v2 endpoints directly instead of going through xurl.\n","thinkingSignature":"a8fbf1be453989dd5397c7b0b1580119367988bc2baaa4082ceabc7f55f03b40"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8tyf1h83lkgv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl auth oauth2 --help 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":381,"output":266,"cacheRead":110912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111559,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777784753467,"responseId":"06460ab1d78f28903e654e79115fc2ed"}}
