{"type":"message","id":"7fd89cf4","parentId":"db43a905","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:06:29.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `xurl auth oauth2` command is interactive - it needs a browser. But it also says `[USERNAME]` as an optional argument. Let me try a different approach - maybe there's a way to pass a refresh token or access token directly.\n\nActually, let me look at the raw X API. If we have a bearer token, we can use app-only auth for read endpoints. Bookmarks require user context though...\n\nActually wait - X API does have a GET /2/users/:id/bookmarks endpoint that works with app-only bearer token for reading bookmarks! Let me check the X API docs.\n\nActually no - the error message said \"OAuth 2.0 User Context\" which means it needs user context, not just app context. \n\nBut we have an OAuth 2 access token from Bobby's setup. I should try passing it directly to the xurl command with the bearer token, or possibly use the refresh token flow to get a fresh OAuth 2 token if the current one is invalid.\n\nLet me try a simpler approach first - I'll write the OAuth 2 token and refresh token directly to the xurl config file and test if that works.\n","thinkingSignature":"1c7f3b25f861858671f63f7b21ca30dae61f1e830bd189ac475e463cc3835c86"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lvp9okh3aev0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Write the OAuth2 tokens to the config file\npython3 -c \"\nimport yaml\n\nconfig_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.xurl')\n\n# Read existing\nwith open(config_path) as f:\n    config = yaml.safe_load(f)\n\n# Add OAuth2 token to xai-prod\nconfig['apps']['xai-prod']['oauth2_token'] = {\n    'type': 'oauth2',\n    'oauth2': {\n        'access_token': 'cHlqQnlEVnlCWFlIOEE5d2EzTkFfVjY2cWsyY0VxQUc5cXMyWEtCUkFXYU9sOjE3Nzc2OTE3MTg0MjM6MTowOmF0OjE',\n        'refresh_token': 'cTlmeWJBMDBaZWdjaHU0aGZYdWRqVTBVUzMwM1hNYldYX3dOc3g5N09qQTVWOjE3Nzc2OTE3MTg0MjM6MToxOnJ0OjE',\n        'client_id': 'WDNldnByaFhyWXhDZ3ZHNGQ0dE06MTpjaQ',\n        'client_secret': '7N67iqkNfrBcMtsmFzzvGkt0KpPaBBJAGSLh2EzgZtLY6fLRcp'\n    }\n}\n\n# Write back\nwith open(config_path, 'w') as f:\n    yaml.dump(config, f)\n\nprint('OAuth2 token added to xai-prod')\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":170,"output":603,"cacheRead":111232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777784770765,"responseId":"06460ac24d72fc975c4ad661f613b324"}}
