{"type":"message","id":"54422825","parentId":"f2d5488e","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:08:39.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OAuth2 token doesn't work for user context either. The problem is the access token I was given seems to be a \"client credentials\" type token rather than a user context token. For bookmarks API, you need a user context token with the right scopes.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The xurl tool supports OAuth2, but the way it gets OAuth2 tokens is through an interactive browser flow (`xurl auth oauth2`). The token Bobby has might not be formatted right or might not have the right scopes.\n\nLet me try a different approach - use the xurl oauth2 command interactively... but that's hard to do in an exec session.\n\nActually, let me check what scopes the current OAuth2 token has by decoding it.\n","thinkingSignature":"7ea3eabf2281fbda0bccae04a68753f1541afda950686949a4a1643682bbc513"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hq766tu0umgf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport base64, json\n\ntoken = 'cHlqQnlEVnlCWFlIOEE5d2EzTkFfVjY2cWsyY0VxQUc5cXMyWEtCUkFXYU9sOjE3Nzc2OTE3MTg0MjM6MTowOmF0OjE'\n# JWT tokens have 3 parts separated by dots\nparts = token.split('.')\nif len(parts) >= 2:\n    # Add padding if needed\n    padded = parts[1] + '=' * (4 - len(parts[1]) % 4)\n    decoded = base64.b64decode(padded)\n    print(json.dumps(json.loads(decoded), indent=2))\nelse:\n    print('Not a JWT, trying raw decode')\n    print(base64.b64decode(token + '=='))\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":158,"output":363,"cacheRead":113728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114249,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777784901200,"responseId":"06460b45c163c77bb0a878dbdf2418ba"}}
